    "id": "8f0cc7a7",
    "skill": "Words in Context",
    "difficulty": "Hard",
    "passage": "Business researcher Melanie Brucks and colleagues found that remote video conference meetings may be less conducive to\nbrainstorming than in-person meetings are. The researchers suspect that video meeting participants are focused on staring at the\nspeaker on the screen and don\u2019t allow their eyes or mind to wander as much, which may ultimately ______ creativity.",
