    "skill": "Words in Context",
    "difficulty": "Hard",
    "passage": "Mineralogical differences are detectable in samples collected from two locations on the near-Earth asteroid Ryugu, but such\ndifferences may not indicate substantial compositional variations in the asteroid. Cosmochemist Kazuhide Nagashima and\ncolleagues note that at the small scale of the samples, the distribution of minerals is unlikely to be ______.",
